name: Loki Wallet v1.0.2
body:
# Overview This is the first release of Loki Wallet - v1.0.2 **Warning: Uninstalling the app will render your wallet files useless unless you have noted the "Restore Password"!** Be aware, that the "CrAzYpass" feature in this release introduces major changes to the password system used by Loki Wallet. The passphrase you use for your wallet is NOT the password used for the wallet files themselves. So if you need to use the wallet files on a new/other device or even the same device after resetting or uninstalling Loki Wallet, you will need to write down the "Restore Password" from the Details-Screen. On the upside, your wallet files are secured by 256-bit keys. This only applies to new wallets & wallets whose passphrase is changed in the app. If something is unclear, please ask. As Loki Wallet is a grateful fork of Monerujo and uses its CrAzYpass password scheme, for understanding how it works, please check out [this article](https://medium.com/@anhdres/how-monerujos-crazypass-crazy-secure-password-scheme-works-dc4f99a99ff0) # Credits * m2049r * 0140454 * anhdres * balstar * bitOMG * Codivorous * el00ruobuob * erciccione * Flenst (with help of Rafficer and lovvskillz) * hrumag * Lafudoci * rehrar * Re-Diculous # Download Hash If you would like to verify that you have downloaded the correct file, please use the following SHA256 hash: * loki-wallet-v1x0x2_universal.apk
4784eb674576e8bc54a8578c2117bdf448ceb9774103b1ca822afe6aabc4c755 * loki-wallet-v1x0x2_arm64-v8a.apk
df39c71779b8400cdeed4d7347025204e8503a5c4d70caafe82d4ca2f815b39b * loki-wallet-v1x0x2_armeabi-v7a.apk
2a097496a037e415c8fbf7c6e3dc4595715d26e06b598af4993d2ad7fc6c3347 * loki-wallet-v1x0x2_x86.apk
a0db749121b08005efd0b21783521849b7fb6c4950f68aebf264b90a134ecc1d * loki-wallet-v1x0x2_x86_64.apk
59036acacf1a93cb0f614dfcc4a1c483e8cf79734d8ec1d57dc9cc4ae7f27192 ## Windows `certUtil -hashfile loki-wallet-*.apk SHA256` ## Linux `sha256sum loki-wallet-*.apk` ## Mac OS `shasum -a 256 loki-wallet-*.apk` # APK Signature The APK signature can be verified using the apksigner bundled with the Android SDK by locating and executing `apksigner verify --print-certs loki-wallet-*.apk` with the following output: ``` Signer #1 certificate DN: CN=Kee Jefferys, OU=Technology, O=Loki, L=Melbourne, ST=Victoria, C=AU Signer #1 certificate SHA-256 digest: 98903aa82e88bee59f51870d8b080a6281ff513cf8a9235fdeb0d7bb218184a8 Signer #1 certificate SHA-1 digest: e6ebb6342bfca1e9b719430ee0e45a49095451d8 Signer #1 certificate MD5 digest: 66bd18832f7c5f90f7fd77e0110e92db ``` # Donations If you want to support Loki Wallet, please consider making a donation to [Monerujo Team](https://github.com/m2049r/xmrwallet)
